      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>I regularly leave for adventure trips with 
>40-60 bone chips on me, and 
>just recast until I get a 
>good pet.  If it's during 
>the day, I'll recast until I 
>get a blue pet that hits 
>at the level just below the 
>top pet, if at night, keep 
>going until I get a top 
>pet, then hand it a dagger. 
>
>I just learned to accept this as 
>one of the things we necromancers 
>have to deal with -- I 
>actually take quite a bit of 
>pride in crafting a powerful pet 
>who can almost do as much 
>damage as a warrior of the 
>same level as me.  Remember, 
>though, that that is only with 
>a top pet and high speed 
>dagger.  It takes some work 
>to get that going, though. 
>Yes, of course green pets are trash. 
> Most of the problems people 
>describe about pets sucking are because 
>they are generating green or low-blue 
>pets. OF COURSE they suck! 
>The general rule is: 
>When you get a new pet spell, 
>re-cast at night in the dark 
>until you find the one that 
>hits the most.  Then, forever 
>more, if it's daytime and you 
>cast, just recast until you get 
>a pet that hits for 2 
>less than that (maybe you'll get 
>lucky and get the top one 
>during the day.)  Then use 
>that one until nighttime and recast 
>until you get your top one. 
> Then settle in for some 
>decent adventure, and keep /pet back 
>off hotkeyed.  (My regular adventuring 
>bank of 6 hot keys is 
>Persona, Sit, Spells, /pet kill, /pet 
>back off, /pet follow me.) 
>For dungeons, learn to lead your pet 
>around, swing wide around corners and 
>wait for it to catch up, 
>and when standing, don't stand such 
>that the pet is trying to 
>walk into the walls -- that 
>has a tendency to make the 
>pet suicide.  Yes, it's a 
>bug, but you can work around 
>it if careful. 
>From what I have heard of the 
>higher-level pets, they are just fine 
>(correct me if I'm wrong.)  
>The only difficulty is in getting 
>the words to make the spells 
>(several copies of the words if 
>necessary.)  Yes, it's idiotic that 
>level 45 necros are running around 
>with a level 34 pet (which 
>may be green to a level 
>34 caster already, keep in mind.) 
> Of course that pet is 
>worthless. 
>It seems to me the gripes are 
>with the inability to get the 
>current pet spells, or with them, 
>to cast a top-end pet.  
>That extra work, which can take 
>upwards of 15 minutes, I take 
>great in-game pride in. 
</TEXTAREA>
     
   </TD></TR>
